The program must accept principal amount P (in Rs), number of years N (in years) and rate of annual interest R (in %) as the input. The program must print the simple interest (in Rs) with precision up to 2 decimal places as the output.
Formula: Simple Interest = (P x N x R) / 100

Input Format:
The first line contains the values of P, N and R separated by space(s).

Output Format:
The first line contains the value of simple interest.

Example Input/Output:
Input:
2000 2 4.5

Output:
180.00


ğŸ…ğŸ…ğŸ…¢ğŸ…¦ğŸ…”ğŸ…¡

#include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>

void main()
{
int P, N;
float R;
scanf("%d %d %f",&P,&N,&R);
printf("%.2f",(P*N*R)/100);
}
